what are periodontal diseases periodontitis formerly known as pyorrhea alveolaris is the name of a collection of inflammatory diseases affecting the tissues that surround and support the teeth periodontitis is inflammation of the periodontium the periodontal ligament gingiva cementum and alveolar bone it usually presents as a worsening of gingivitis symptoms are rare except with hiv or when abscesses develop in which pain and swelling are common diagnosis is based on inspection periodontal probing and x rays treatment involves dental cleaning that extends under the gums and a vigorous home hygiene program advanced cases may require antibiotics and surgery please see the web pages for more details on periodontitis Gingivitis Dentistry Periodontal ligament Dental caries Chronic fatigue syndrome Tooth enamel Pneumonia Oral hygiene Abscess Tooth Osteoarthritis Crohn's disease Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Colorectal cancer Prostate cancer Group A streptococcal infection Cellulitis Rheumatoid arthritis Ulcerative colitis Gonorrhoea Inflammatory bowel disease Inflammation Acne Diarrhea Allergy Coeliac disease Traumatic brain injury Pelvic inflammatory disease Breast cancer Mastoiditis Peptic ulcer Aortic dissection Penis Breast Atherosclerosis Cancer Guillain-Barr__ syndrome Endometriosis Tuberculosis Medicine Carpal tunnel syndrome Leukemia Medical analysis of circumcision Asthma Dental implant Gout AIDS Lymphogranuloma venereum Paget's disease of bone Emphysema Psoriasis Brain abscess Sickle-cell disease Hip fracture Surgery Lupus erythematosus Erysipelas Lung cancer Dentures Esophageal cancer Autoimmune diseases Hemorrhoid Cervical cancer Cirrhosis Phimosis Bone marrow transplant Hirschsprung's disease Cardiovascular disease Conjunctivitis Urinary incontinence IgA nephropathy Cholecystitis Gastroesophageal reflux disease Diverticulitis Radiation therapy Mesothelioma Renal cell carcinoma Rheumatic fever Halitosis Liver Anemia Meningitis HIV test Wegener's granulomatosis Hodgki